  "prompt": "What is the average CPF cash balance for a member at the age of 55 in Singapore?",
  "response": "As of my latest information, the average CPF (Central Provident Fund) cash balance for a member at the age of 55 in Singapore can vary based on several factors, including the individual's income, contributions, employment history, and usage of CPF funds for housing, healthcare, and education.\n\nHowever, specific and recent average balance figures are generally released by the CPF Board or the Ministry of Manpower in their annual reports or statistics updates. You may want to refer to these official sources or contact the CPF Board directly for the most accurate and up-to-date figures.",
